name: yarn.app.mapreduce.client-am.ipc.max-retries-on-timeouts
description:
The number of client retries on socket timeouts to the AM - before
    reconnecting to the RM to fetch Application Status.
    In other words, it is the ipc.client.connect.max.retries.on.timeouts to be used during
    reconnecting to the RM and fetching Application Status.

name: file.client-write-packet-size
description: Packet size for clients to write

name: mapreduce.shuffle.pathcache.max-weight
description: The maximum total weight of entries the cache may contain.

name: dfs.namenode.block.deletion.increment
description:
The number of block deletion increment.
      This setting will control the block increment deletion rate to
      ensure that other waiters on the lock can get in.

name: dfs.qjournal.http.read.timeout.ms
description:
Timeout in milliseconds when reading from a HTTP connection from remote
    journals.

name: mapreduce.job.cache.limit.max-single-resource-mb
description:
The maximum size (in MB) of a single resource a map reduce job
    is allow to submit for localization via files, libjars, archives, and
    jobjar command line arguments and through the distributed cache. If set to
    0 the limit is ignored.

name: nfs.wtmax
description:
This is the maximum size in bytes of a WRITE request
    supported by the NFS gateway. If you change this, make sure you
    also update the nfs mount's wsize(add wsize= # of bytes to the 
    mount directive).
